# {{ .ProjectName }} - Arbitrum L2 Stack

A production-quality Arbitrum L2 development stack built with Solidity ^0.8.20. Includes cross-chain messaging, token bridging, and gas-efficient contracts. All contracts are standalone with no external dependencies.

## Architecture

This template includes four core modules for Arbitrum L2 development:

### 1. Token (`contracts/token/ArbitrumToken.sol`)
Gas-efficient ERC-20 token optimized for Arbitrum L2:
- Standard `transfer`, `approve`, `transferFrom`
- Owner-controlled `mint` and permissionless `burn`
- Gas-optimized storage layout for L2 cost reduction
- Batch transfer support for multi-recipient distributions

### 2. L1-to-L2 Bridge Messaging (`contracts/bridge/L1ToL2MessageSender.sol`)
Contract for sending messages from L1 to Arbitrum L2:
- Retryable ticket creation for guaranteed L2 execution
- Configurable gas parameters for L2 execution
- Message tracking with unique ticket IDs
- Owner-managed L2 target configuration

### 3. L2-to-L1 Bridge Messaging (`contracts/bridge/L2ToL1MessageSender.sol`)
Contract for sending messages from Arbitrum L2 back to L1:
- Outbox-based message passing via ArbSys precompile
- Message nonce tracking for replay protection
- Configurable L1 target addresses
- Event-based message confirmation

### 4. Token Gateway (`contracts/gateway/TokenGateway.sol`)
Bidirectional token bridging between L1 and L2:
- Deposit tokens from L1 to L2 with automatic minting
- Withdraw tokens from L2 to L1 with burn-and-release
- Paired L1/L2 gateway architecture
- Configurable token mappings between layers

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- [Foundry](https://book.getfoundry.sh/getting-started/installation)
- Node.js >= 16 (for deploy scripts)

### Build
```bash
forge build
```

### Test
```bash
forge test -vvv
```

### Deploy (local Arbitrum fork)
```bash
# Start a local Arbitrum fork
dokrypt up

# Deploy contracts
npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.js --network localhost

# Bridge tokens
npx hardhat run scripts/bridge-tokens.js --network localhost
```

## Project Structure

```
contracts/
  token/
    ArbitrumToken.sol        # Gas-efficient ERC-20 for Arbitrum
  bridge/
    L1ToL2MessageSender.sol  # L1 -> L2 message sender
    L2ToL1MessageSender.sol  # L2 -> L1 message sender
  gateway/
    TokenGateway.sol         # Token bridging gateway

test/
  ArbitrumToken.t.sol        # Token tests
  L1ToL2Message.t.sol        # L1 -> L2 message tests
  TokenGateway.t.sol         # Gateway tests

scripts/
  deploy.js                  # Contract deployment
  bridge-tokens.js           # Token bridging operations
```

## Security Notes

- All contracts include reentrancy guards on state-changing functions
- Bridge messaging contracts validate sender addresses to prevent unauthorized cross-chain calls
- The token gateway enforces balance checks before and after every bridge operation
- Message nonces prevent replay attacks on cross-chain messages
- No external imports or dependencies -- all code is self-contained

## Configuration

See `dokrypt.yaml` for chain configuration and `foundry.toml` for compiler settings.

